# Deploying a production server that predicts the churn value for new customers

# Instructions on Running the churn model:

- Clone the repo 
- cd/churn_project/flask-deployment-waitress+gunicorn
- pip install -r requirements.txt

# For Windows users, Waitress will run the app:
 on your terminal run the code below
- waitress-serve --listen=0.0.0.0:9696 predict_svc:app

open the marketsvc.ipynb and run the chunks to interact with the deployed model
- You can alter the customer details for different prediction responses


# Instruction on using gunicorn with windows sub system for linux (WSL) for deployment
- Install wsl on your windows computer.
  Follow instructions outlined here to install wsl for your system -> https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install 
- copy all files in /flask-deployment-waitress+gunicorn from your local onto your wsl home dir and run 
- gunicorn --bind 0.0.0.0:9696 predict_svc:app
